decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - Three year time limit
The development hereby permitted shall be begun within 3 years from the date of this permission.
Reason: In order to comply with Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, as amended by Section 51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004.
Condition : 2 - In accordance with approved drawings
The proposed development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with:
Documents received on 16/12/2024
Site Location Plan (Area leased by HVFC); HV02-01 (Current Layout And Topographical Survey); Location Plan dated 16/11/2024; HV02-02 (Site Area); Construction Method Statement And Site Management Plan, by blakedown sport & play; Transport Assessment And Statement dated December 2024, by Paul Hawkins Development; HV02/03 (New 3G synthetic turf pitch); BSP-HVFC-001 Rev C (Preliminary Design); 20241215 V2.0 Hanworth FC the Statutory Biodiversity Metric Calculation Tool 23.07.2024.xlsx; Planning Statement Incorporating the Design And Access Statement dated December 2024, by Paul Hawkins Development; Fire Emergency Plan dated Aug 2023 (Updated Oct 2024), by Hanworth Villa Football Club; Fire Statement dated December 2024, by Paul Hawkins Development
Documents received on 20/12/2024
Flood map for planning dated 25/11/2024, by Environment Agency; Biodiversity Net Gain Assessment V2, dated 15 December 2024 by Sylvatica Ecology Ltd; Flood Risk Assessment and Drainage Strategy Revision B, dated: December 2024 by JPP
Documents received on 28/01/2025
-	Noise Impact Assessment (NP-012109) dated 21/01/2025, by Nova Acoustics
Documents received on 02/01/2025
Revised Construction Management Plan, by blakedown sport & play
Documents received on 03/03/2025
Additional information on Transport, by Hanworth Villa FC 
Reason: To ensure the development is carried out in accordance with the planning permission, a satisfactory standard of development is secured and to allow the local planning authority to review any potential changes to the scheme.
Condition : 3 - Materials
Notwithstanding any information given in the documents hereby approved, the materials to be used in implementation of the proposed scheme hereby permitted shall be 3G Artificial Turf Pitch to comply with performance requirements of FIFA Quality standard and be placed on the FA Register of 3G pitches. 
Reason: In order that the Council may be satisfied as to the details of the development in the interests of the amenity of the area and pitch users, to satisfy the requirements of policies indicated in this report. 
Condition : 4 - Lighting 
Lighting shall be designed, positioned and directed so as not to unnecessarily intrude on passing drivers or pedestrians or direct light into any neighbouring windows in accordance with the guidance provided by the Institute of Lighting Engineers Guidance Note: For The Reduction Of Obtrusive Light 2021.
Reason: In order to protect neighbours' living conditions and in the interests of highway safety
Condition : 5 - Cycle storage
Prior to the first use of the development, full details (including manufacturers' specifications) of secure covered cycle parking facilities that accord with the Guidance for the staff, members and visitors to the development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. 
The approved facilities shall be fully implemented and made available for use before the development is first occupied or brought into use, The approved facilities shall be thereafter retained for use at all times without obstruction.
Reason: In order to support sustainable transport objectives.
Condition : 6 - Travel Plan 
Before the development hereby permitted is first occupied or brought into use, a Travel Plan in accordance with current Council and TfL guidance comprising immediate, continuing and long-term measures to promote and encourage a reduction in car use shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. 
The approved Travel Plan shall be implemented upon occupation, and thereafter monitored and reviewed in accordance with the agreed Travel Plan targets and timescales to the satisfaction of the Local Planning Authority.
Reason: In order to support sustainable transport objectives, including a reduction in single occupancy car journeys and the increased use of public transport, walking and cycling.
Condition : 7 - Car parking management
Before the development hereby permitted is first occupied or brought into use, a Parking Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Plan shall include the following:
(i)	Details of changes to car parking on site by the development (for members, staff, blue badge holders and visitors of the site) and how this will be operated and enforced
(ii)	details of measures proposed to restrict parking to designated bays only and prohibit parking on the access road
(iii)	a commitment to convert passive EV bays to active when demand requires.
(iv)	details of the operation of any gates or barriers
The parking areas and access road(s) shall thereafter be managed in compliance with the approved Parking Management Plan unless the prior written approval of the local planning authority is obtained to secure any variation.
Reason: In order to promote sustainable modes of transport, to protect neighbours' living conditions and to ensure minimal disruption of traffic in the locality.
Condition : 8 - Construction Management Plan
No development shall take place until a Construction Logistics Plan (CLP), written in accordance with current TfL guidance, has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The CLP shall include
1.	a site plan
2.	confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused
3.	provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors
4.	provisions for loading, unloading and storage of plant and materials within the site
5.	details of access to the site, including means to control and manage access and egress of vehicles to and from the site for the duration of construction including phasing arrangements
6.	details of vehicle routeing from the site to the wider strategic road network
7.	provision of wheel washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads when required and at the request of the council
8. measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway especially cyclists and pedestrians in the vicinity of the site and especially at the access
9. avoidance of peak hours for deliveries and details of a booking system to avoid vehicles waiting on the public highway
The approved CLP shall be adhered to throughout the construction period for the development.
Reason: In order to ensure highway safety is maintained and preserved and to safeguard the amenities of adjoining residential properties. 
Condition : 9 - .Ecological Management Plan
No development shall take place after installation of new 3G synthetic turf pitch until an Ecological Management Plan has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. 
 The Ecological Management Plan shall incorporate:   
i.	details of measures to protect breeding birds, nests and eggs from mortality/damage, injury and disturbance, including avoidance by timing and/or appropriate supervision. 
ii.	an ecological lighting plan; 
iii.	details of how the enhancement measures will be monitored, managed and maintained, including the long- term design objectives, management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for 5 years; 
iv.	species surveys within and around the site to demonstrate ecological enhancements 
v.	mitigating measures on how to stop microplastics from new 3G synthetic turf pitch
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details. 
Reason: In the interests of nature conservation. 
Condition : 10 - Construction Hours
No demolition or construction work shall take place on the site except between the hours of Monday to Friday 07:30 � 16:30, Saturday 08:00 � 13:00; and, no Sunday, bank holiday or public holiday working.
The Council may exercise its powers and penalties under environmental legislation to take enforcement action against developers who ignore this requirement.
Reason: In the interests of amenity.
Condition : 11 - Drainage 

No part of the development hereby approved shall be occupied until evidence (photographs and copies of installation contracts, along with a written confirmation) has been submitted to the local planning authority and approved in writing to demonstrate that the sustainable drainage scheme hereby approved has been completed in accordance with the submitted final detailed drainage designs. The sustainable drainage scheme shall be managed and maintained thereafter in accordance with the agreed management and maintenance plan for all of the proposed drainage components.

Reason: In order to ensure that the methods to mitigate the risk of surface water flooding have been implemented as agreed and that the drainage system is suitably managed.

Condition : 12 - Biodiversity Net Gain 
Prior to the first commencement of the hereby approved development, a Biodiversity Gain Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, the Plan shall include; 
(a) information about the steps taken or to be taken to minimise the adverse effect of the development on the biodiversity of the onsite habitat and any other habitat, 
(b) the pre-development biodiversity value of the onsite habitat, 
(c) the post-development biodiversity value of the onsite habitat,
(d) any registered offsite biodiversity gain allocated to the development, and the biodiversity value of that gain in relation to the development, 
(e) any biodiversity credits purchased for the development, and 
(f) such other matters as the Secretary of State may by regulations specify. 
The development shall thereafter be carried out in accordance with the approved Plan prior to the first occupation of the development. Any habitats created or enhanced on-site and off-site in accordance with the Biodiversity Gain Plan must be maintained thereafter for a minimum of 30 years. 
Reason. In the interests of improving Biodiversity and in accordance with The Town and Country Planning Act 1990, Section 90A, Schedule 7A.
description: Installation of a 3G synthetic turf football pitch and extending the existing floodlights time from 14:00 - 22:00 three days a week to 7 days a week.
